{"id": "EUVD-2021-34353", "enisaUuid": "f375162a-13db-3604-b359-3a8c9c3babe1", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/amd/display: Avoid HDCP over-read and corruption\n\nInstead of reading the desired 5 bytes of the actual target field,\nthe code was reading 8. This could result in a corrupted value if the\ntrailing 3 bytes were non-zero, so instead use an appropriately sized\nand zero-initialized bounce buffer, and read only 5 bytes before casting\nto u64.", "datePublished": "2024-05-21T14:35:53", "dateUpdated": "2025-09-15T12:14:05", "baseScore": 9.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c5b518f4b98dbb2bc31b6a55e6aaa1e0e2948f2e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/44c7c901cb368a9f2493748f213b247b5872639f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3b2b93a485fb7a970bc8b5daef16f4cf579d172f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/06888d571b513cbfc0b41949948def6cb81021b2"], "aliases": ["CVE-2021-47348"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "02986ed6-e5e4-3520-bcd4-e0682c2bc6de", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <c5b518f4b98dbb2bc31b6a55e6aaa1e0e2948f2e"}, {"id": "1140f63f-5293-3201-9fb1-edf8ebe84f01", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4c283fdac08abf3211533f70623c90a34f41d08d <c5b518f4b98dbb2bc31b6a55e6aaa1e0e2948f2e"}, {"id": "1d373b6a-7b1a-36a3-983a-06d25e01b5d7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <06888d571b513cbfc0b41949948def6cb81021b2"}, {"id": "27dd8863-7a66-35ad-8cb3-2f1eca90be7a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4c283fdac08abf3211533f70623c90a34f41d08d <44c7c901cb368a9f2493748f213b247b5872639f"}, {"id": "31e6dcdb-2222-387a-97d5-6bf5ce41d85a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.13.3"}, {"id": "3618f2c6-acea-3a48-ab37-bed781b7e20